history.content: I would recommend taking 61C first. Students definitely have done well in 162 without 61C, but 61C really helps getting you to think about parallelism and introduces you to concepts like the stack, address translation, caching, assembly instructions, etc that students are assumed to already know. Especially in the summer, it might be tough to have to learn those concepts for the first time when the course is going so fast.

Is it even remotely possible to take 162 this summer (su19) without having completed 61C?

If so, are there any resources recommended for preparation? Thanks!

(I'm either taking 162 OR 61C + some RnB)
history.subject: CS 162 w/o CS 61C
